The Monetary Policy Committee of the Central Bank of Nigeria on Thursday reduced the Monetary Policy Rate to 12.5 per cent, The PUNCH reports. The CBN Governor, Mr Godwin Emefiele, announced the decision of the Committee in Abuja, at the end of its virtual 273rd meeting. The committee had retained the MPR at 13.5 per cent at the last MPC meeting in March. It, however, retained the Cash Reserve Ratio and the liquidity ratio at 27.5 per cent and 30 per cent respectively. Details later… By Nse Anthony-Uko ABUJA, (Sundiata Post) -- The Central Bank of Nigeria has kept its key interest rate at 14 per cent, in line with market expectations as the country fights off future recession threats. CBN Governor, Mr Godwin Emefiele stated that Nigeria’s economic indicators remain positive despite MPC meeting… September 25, 2018 In "Business" By Fabian Ekeruche Lagos -   Alhaji Aminu Gwadabe, a financial expert, has urged the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) to further mop up excess Naira in circulation to sustain its stability. The advice came ahead of the Monetary Policy Committee (MPC) meeting of the bank scheduled for July 24… July 21, 2017 In "Top Stories" Abuja- The Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) on Tuesday in Abuja announced devaluation of naira by N13 as part of measures the bank said were aimed at strengthening the nation’s economy. The CBN Governor, Mr Godwin Emefiele, disclosed the devaluation to newsmen after a meeting of the Monetary Policy Committee.… November 25, 2014 In "Business"